As Jandebeur explained to Fox News: 'I pulled out my automatic and was getting ready to ventilate him.

'Once he saw my gun, he decided it was time to leave.'

Jandebeur said his wife was actually sitting in the passenger seat of his truck waiting for him

He said he was concerned for both of them.

However he is thankful to have had his gun, and that his business is situated in a gun zone.

'Anybody that doesn't arm themselves is asking for trouble,' he said.

